          .card-key-item.l-box
            h1.card-key-title Ace
            p.card-key-description 
              strong Waterfall. 
              | All players begin drinking. The player to your left cannot stop until you stop. The player to their left cannot stop until they stop. So and so forth until the last person.
              | <br/>Optionally, a waterfall can move to the right instead of left. Determine the direction by asking a trivia question to the players on your left and right. The winner will follow you instead of being last.
        .pure-u-1.pure-u-md-1-2
          .card-key-item.l-box
            h1.card-key-title King
            p.card-key-description 
              strong Make a rule.  
              | Each one will carry over the rest of the game, unless another rule is made that vetoes it. Also, we can <a href="/rule">help</a> in case you can't think of one. 
        .pure-u-1.pure-u-md-1-2
          .card-key-item.l-box
            h1.card-key-title Queen
            p.card-key-description
              strong Question Master. 
              | Anytime you ask someone a question and that person answers that question, that person drinks. You continue being the Question Master until the next queen is drawn.
        .pure-u-1.pure-u-md-1-2
          .card-key-item.l-box
            h1.card-key-title Jack
            p.card-key-description
              strong Categories. 
              | Think of a good category. Like candy bars. Go in a circle, each person naming a different member of that category. First person to blank out drinks.
        .pure-u-1.pure-u-md-1-2
